  article#dropdown
    h1 #[a(href='#dropdown') Dropdown]
    p Dropdown is a list of items that appears when user click on.
    div
      article#dropdown-simple
        h2 #[a(href='#dropdown-simple') Simple dropdown]
        p There are two basic classes: #[code.html .dropdown--out] and #[code.html .dropdown--in]. The first one has absolutely positioned content and second one has content inside menu so when dropdown is clicked then content below will slide down to make place. Moreover the first one can have one of four additional class: #[code.html .dropdown--down] #[code.html .dropdown--up] #[code.html .dropdown--left] #[code.html .dropdown--right]. It determines on which side of container content will appear.
        .row
          .ddm-position-opt.col-xs-6
            h3 Content position
            .input-group
              input(type='radio' name='dd-pos' data-class-name='--down' checked)#dd-pos-1
              label(for='dd-pos-1') Down
            .input-group
              input(type='radio' name='dd-pos' data-class-name='--up')#dd-pos-2
              label(for='dd-pos-2') Up
            .input-group
              input(type='radio' name='dd-pos' data-class-name='--left')#dd-pos-3
              label(for='dd-pos-3') Left
            .input-group
              input(type='radio' name='dd-pos' data-class-name='--right')#dd-pos-4
              label(for='dd-pos-4') Right
          .ddm-theme-opt.col-xs-6
            h3 Themes
            .input-group
              input(type='checkbox' name='dd-themes' data-class-name='dropdown--blue' checked=true)#dd-themes-1
              label(for='dd-themes-1') Add theme

        div.dropdown.first-dd.dropdown--out.dropdown--down.dropdown--blue(style='width:30%')
