    h1 #[a(href='#tabs') Tabs]
    p Like in #[a(href='#accordion') accordion], this component is used to show informations in limited amount of space. Instead of accordion, tabs shows data in form of table or bookmarks. #[strong Note:] Because of absolute positioning of each tab content it need to set to the #[code.html .tab__content] class height property (default: 200px) and equivalent #[code.html margin-bottom] for tabs container.
    div
      .row
        .tabs-width-opt.col-xs-6
          h3 Width options
          .input-group
            input(type='radio' name='tabs-width' data-class-name="--full-width" checked=true)#tabs-width-1
            label(for='tabs-width-1') Full width
          div.input-group
            input(type='radio' name='tabs-width' data-class-name="--fixed-width")#tabs-width-2
            label(for='tabs-width-2') Fixed width - default 70%
        .tabs-theme-opt.col-xs-6
          h3 Theme
          .input-group
            input(type='checkbox' name='tabs-theme' data-class-name="tabs--blue" checked=true)#tabs-theme
            label(for='tabs-theme') Theme

      ul.tabs.tabs--full-width.tabs--blue
        each tab in site.data.tabs
          li
            input(type=tab.input.type, name=tab.input.name, id=tab.input.id, checked=tab.input.checked)
            label(for=tab.input.id) #{tab.input.id.replace('s-', ' ')}
            .tab__content(class=tab.input.scrollable ? "tab__content--scrollable" : "")
              h2 #{tab.content.heading}
              p #{tab.content.paragraph}
